OL,4,CThailand bans coral-damaging sunscreens
OL,5,Cin marine parks
OL,6, Thailand has banned sunscreens
OL,7, containing chemicals that damage coral
OL,8, from all of its marine national parks.
OL,10,FConcerns are growing that lotions
OL,11,Ftourists use for sun protection are
OL,12,Fharming slow-growing corals.
OL,14,FThe Thai Department of Conservation
OL,15,Fsaid four ingredients commonly found in
OL,16,Fsun creams were shown to destroy coral
OL,17,Flarvae, obstruct coral reproduction and
OL,18,Fcause reef bleaching.
OL,20,FAnyone flouting the ban can be fined up
OL,21,Fto 100,000 baht (#2,100).
